{"title_page": "Kirsten Prout", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Kirsten Prout\n| image = Kirsten Prout at MTV Movie Awards 2012.jpg\n| caption = Prout interviewed at the [[MTV Movie Awards]] in 2012\n| birth_name = Kirsten Prout\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1990|9|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], Canada\n| other_names = Kirsten Zien\n| nationality = [[Canadians|Canadian]]\n| occupation = Actress\n| yearsactive = 2000&ndash;present\n| spouse = {{marriage|Matt Zien|2017}}\n}}\n\n'''Kirsten Prout Zien''' (born September 28, 1990) is a Canadian actress. She is known for her lead roles in the [[ABC Family]] television shows, ''[[Kyle XY]]'' and ''[[The Lying Game]]''. Her first sizable break in film came in 2005, when she was cast as Abby Miller, a lead role opposite Jennifer Garner in ''[[Elektra (2005 film)|Elektra]]''. In 2007, Prout was nominated for Best Performance in a TV Series by the Young Artists Awards for her portrayal of Amanda Bloom in ''[[Kyle XY]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nProut began her acting career at the age of 10 after being cast in a commercial opposite NHL superstar [[Wayne Gretzky]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kidzworld.com/article/8166-kirsten-prout-interview|title=Kirsten Prout Interview|work=Kidzworld|access-date=2017-06-14|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=KirstenProutNet|title=Kirsten Prout first acting job|date=2012-08-23|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zcHLetL0ebA|accessdate=2017-06-14}}</ref> Speaking about her desire to start acting, Kirsten recalled that it was the only way she thought she could turn being a Disney Princess into a career.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nProut graduated high school from [[Collingwood School]] in [[West Vancouver|West Vancouver, British Columbia]], Canada, along with actors [[Alexander Ludwig]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vancouverobserver.com/blogs/tmi/2012/03/22/actor-alexander-ludwig-says-hunger-games-discourages-violence|title=Actor Alexander Ludwig says Hunger Games discourages violence|website=The Vancouver Observer|language=en|access-date=2017-06-14}}</ref> and [[Mackenzie Davis]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://vancouversun.com/entertainment/local-arts/metamorphosis-from-north-van-to-blade-runner-2-rising-star-mackenzie-davis-is-happy-being-herself|title=Metamorphosis: From North Van to Blade Runner 2, rising star Mackenzie Davis is happy being herself|date=2016-08-19|work=Vancouver Sun|access-date=2017-06-14|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAn avid martial artist, Kirsten received a [[Black belt (martial arts)|Black Belt]] in [[Taekwondo]] at the age of 13. That year, she was cast in ''[[Elektra (2005 film)|Elektra]]'', and performed her own stunts in the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.craveonline.com/girl/kirsten-prout|title=Girls - CraveOnline|website=CraveOnline|language=en-US|access-date=2017-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203083502/http://www.craveonline.com/girl/kirsten-prout|archive-date=2017-12-03|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAfter completing high school and the final season of ''[[Kyle XY]]'', Prout attended [[McGill University]], where she majored in [[English literature]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.pressreader.com/canada/the-province/20090224/282295316104884|title=TV Star Tackles Studies at McGill|last=Schaefer|first=Glen|date=February 24, 2009|work=The Province|access-date=June 13, 2017}}</ref> In an interview with [[The Province]], then 18-year-old Prout said of attending University: <blockquote>\"I grew up on sets where I was treated like I was 25... In university you're in classes with incredibly intelligent people. You realize you're not an expert on everything.\"<ref name=\":1\" /> </blockquote>\n\n==Career==\nAt the age of 13, Prout made her feature film debut in a lead role as Abigail \"Abby\" Miller in the 2005 film ''[[Elektra (2005 film)|Elektra]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eguide-online.de/kylexy/index.php?seite=artikel&aktion=show&id2=420|title=Exclusive Interview with Kirsten Prout|date=2009-08-22|publisher=eGuide Network|accessdate=2010-01-04}}</ref> The film's Producer Gary Foster said of discovering Prout: \n<blockquote>\"We did a big search... and frankly LA or New York, we thought we'd find somebody there. She came in and auditioned and we were blown away.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.joblo.com/movie-news/set-visit-elektra-33|title=Set Visit: Elektra (3/3)|access-date=2017-06-14|language=en-US}}</ref> </blockquote>\nProut has had lead roles or guest stars in 39 different film and television productions. Her most notable lead roles include \"Amanda Bloom\" in [[Abc family|ABC Family]]'s ''[[Kyle XY]]'', Alex Bell in MTV's ''[[My Super Psycho Sweet 16]]'' comedy-horror trilogy, and \"Char Chamberlin\" in ABC Family's ''[[The Lying Game]]''. Her most notable guest stars include roles in ''[[Stargate SG-1]], [[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]], [[Psych]], [[Devious Maids]],'' and ''[[Dear White People (TV series)|Dear White People]].''{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==Personal life==\nOn October 13, 2017, Prout announced her engagement to [[Development executive|television development executive]] Matt Zien.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BaNTmIuBWIf/|title=Kirsten Prout on Instagram|work=[[Instagram]]|date=October 13, 2017|accessdate=2017-10-25}}</ref> They were married on November 6, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BbMqYMlBNgs/|title=Kirsten Prout on Instagram|work=[[Instagram]]|date=November 7, 2017|accessdate=2017-11-07}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2001 \n| ''[[Mindstorm (film)|Mindstorm]]'' \n| Young Tracy Wellman \n|\n|-\n| 2001 \n| ''De grot''\n| Julie \n| Uncredited\n|-\n| 2005 \n| ''[[Elektra (2005 film)|Elektra]]'' \n| Abigail \"Abby\" Miller \n| \n|-\n| 2008 \n| ''Class Savage'' \n| Julye \n| Short film\n|-\n| 2010 \n| ''[[The Twilight Saga: Eclipse]]'' \n| Lucy \n|\n|-\n| 2013 \n| ''[[No Clue]]'' \n| Reese \n| \n|-\n| 2014 \n| ''[[Joy Ride 3: Roadkill]]'' \n| Jewel McCaul \n| Direct to video\n|-\n| 2015 \n| ''Even Lambs Have Teeth'' \n| Sloane\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''Captured''\n| Nicole \n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2000 \n| ''[[The Linda McCartney Story]]'' \n| Stella \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[First Wave (TV series)|First Wave]]''\n| Emily\n| Episode: \"Wednesday's Child\"\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Once Upon a Christmas (film)|Once Upon a Christmas]]'' \n| Brittney Morgan \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Mysterious Ways (TV series)|Mysterious Ways]]''\n| Lindsay Kasper\n| Episode: \"Wonderful\" \n|-\n| 2001 \n| ''The Wedding Dress'' \n| Stella Carver \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Twice Upon a Christmas]]'' \n| Brittney Morgan \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Jeremiah (TV series)|Jeremiah]]'' \n| Elayna \n| Episode: \"The Touch\"\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Beyond Belief: Fact or Fiction]]''\n| Katie\n| Episode: \"Shared Vision\"\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[The Dead Zone (TV series)|The Dead Zone]]''\n| Susan Reed\n| Episode: \"Here There Be Monsters\"\n|-\n| 2003 \n| ''[[Stargate SG-1]]'' \n| Nesa \n| Episode: \"Birthright\"\n|-\n| 2004 \n| ''The Love Crimes of Gillian Guess'' \n| Amanda Guess \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Cold Squad]]''\n| Ashley\n| Episode: \"The Filth\"\n|-\n| 2006\u20132009 \n| ''[[Kyle XY]]'' \n| Amanda Bloom \n| Main role, 39 episodes\n|-\n| 2007 \n| ''Witness to Murder'' \n| Samantha Cooper \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Meteor Storm]]'' \n| Kara \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Locked Away'' \n| Taylin \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Seven Deadly Sins'' \n| Miranda Stevens\n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[My Super Psycho Sweet 16: Part 2]]'' \n| Alex Bell\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2011\u20132012 \n| ''[[The Lying Game]]'' \n| Charlotte \"Char\" Chamberlin \n| Main role, 12 episodes\n|-\n| 2012 \n| ''[[My Super Psycho Sweet 16: Part 3]]'' \n| Alex Bell \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]'' \n| Lydia Wade \n| Episode: \"[[Gone (NCIS)|Gone]]\"\n|-\n| 2013 \n| ''[[Psych]]'' \n| Zola \n| Episode: \"Cirque du Soul\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Devious Maids]]'' \n| Allison \n| Episode: \"Taking Out the Trash\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Social Nightmare'' \n| Catherine Hardy \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2015 \n| ''My Life as a Dead Girl'' \n| Chelsea White\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''The Wrong Girl''\n| Michelle Foley \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Ties That Bind (TV series)|Ties That Bind]]'' \n| Chelsea Boyd \n| Episode: \"The Whole Picture\"\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Dear White People (TV series)|Dear White People]]'' \n| Emily \n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Woman of the House''\n| Sara Weiss\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''The Christmas Train''\n| Julie\n| Television film\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Music videos ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Artist\n! Role\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}} \n|-\n| 2010\n| \"Starlight\"\n| [[The Framework]]\n| Juliette\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=The Framework \u2013 Starlight (Director's Cut)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yxWYolEqO7A|via=[[YouTube]]|access-date=October 20, 2018}}</ref> \n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0698977|Kirsten Zien}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zien, Kirsten}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Canadian child actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian expatriate actresses in the United States]]\n[[Category:Canadian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:McGill University alumni]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Vancouver]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Kirsten Prout\n| image = Kirsten Prout at MTV Movie Awards 2012.jpg\n| caption = Prout interviewed at the [[MTV Movie Awards]] in 2012\n| birth_name = Kirsten Prout\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1990|9|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], Canada\n| other_names = Kirsten Zien\n| nationality = [[Canadians|Canadian]]\n| occupation = Actress\n| yearsactive = 2000&ndash;present\n| spouse = {{marriage|Matt Zien|2017}}\n}}\n\n'''Kirsten Prout Zien''' (born September 28, 1990) is a Canadian actress. She is known for her lead roles in the [[ABC Family]] television shows, ''[[Kyle XY]]'' and ''[[The Lying Game]]''. Her first sizable break in film came in 2005, when she was cast as Abby Miller, a lead role opposite Jennifer Garner in ''[[Elektra (2005 film)|Elektra]]''. In 2007, Prout was nominated for Best Performance in a TV Series by the Young Artists Awards for her portrayal of Amanda Bloom in ''[[Kyle XY]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nProut began her acting career at the age of 10 after being cast in a commercial opposite NHL superstar [[Wayne Gretzky]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kidzworld.com/article/8166-kirsten-prout-interview|title=Kirsten Prout Interview|work=Kidzworld|access-date=2017-06-14|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=KirstenProutNet|title=Kirsten Prout first acting job|date=2012-08-23|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zcHLetL0ebA|accessdate=2017-06-14}}</ref> Speaking about her desire to start acting, Kirsten recalled that it was the only way she thought she could turn being a Disney Princess into a career.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nProut graduated high school from [[Collingwood School]] in [[West Vancouver|West Vancouver, British Columbia]], Canada, along with actors [[Alexander Ludwig]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vancouverobserver.com/blogs/tmi/2012/03/22/actor-alexander-ludwig-says-hunger-games-discourages-violence|title=Actor Alexander Ludwig says Hunger Games discourages violence|website=The Vancouver Observer|language=en|access-date=2017-06-14}}</ref> and [[Mackenzie Davis]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://vancouversun.com/entertainment/local-arts/metamorphosis-from-north-van-to-blade-runner-2-rising-star-mackenzie-davis-is-happy-being-herself|title=Metamorphosis: From North Van to Blade Runner 2, rising star Mackenzie Davis is happy being herself|date=2016-08-19|work=Vancouver Sun|access-date=2017-06-14|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAn avid martial artist, Kirsten received a [[Black belt (martial arts)|Black Belt]] in [[Taekwondo]] at the age of 13. That year, she was cast in ''[[Elektra (2005 film)|Elektra]]'', and performed her own stunts in the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.craveonline.com/girl/kirsten-prout|title=Girls - CraveOnline|website=CraveOnline|language=en-US|access-date=2017-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203083502/http://www.craveonline.com/girl/kirsten-prout|archive-date=2017-12-03|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAfter completing high school and the final season of ''[[Kyle XY]]'', Prout attended [[McGill University]], where she majored in [[English literature]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.pressreader.com/canada/the-province/20090224/282295316104884|title=TV Star Tackles Studies at McGill|last=Schaefer|first=Glen|date=February 24, 2009|work=The Province|access-date=June 13, 2017}}</ref> In an interview with [[The Province]], then 18-year-old Prout said of attending University: <blockquote>\"I grew up on sets where I was treated like I was 25... In university you're in classes with incredibly intelligent people. You realize you're not an expert on everything.\"<ref name=\":1\" /> </blockquote>\n\n==Career==\nAt the age of 13, Prout made her feature film debut in a lead role as Abigail \"Abby\" Miller in the 2005 film ''[[Elektra (2005 film)|Elektra]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eguide-online.de/kylexy/index.php?seite=artikel&aktion=show&id2=420|title=Exclusive Interview with Kirsten Prout|date=2009-08-22|publisher=eGuide Network|accessdate=2010-01-04}}</ref> The film's Producer Gary Foster said of discovering Prout: \n<blockquote>\"We did a big search... and frankly LA or New York, we thought we'd find somebody there. She came in and auditioned and we were blown away.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.joblo.com/movie-news/set-visit-elektra-33|title=Set Visit: Elektra (3/3)|access-date=2017-06-14|language=en-US}}</ref> </blockquote>\nProut has had lead roles or guest stars in 39 different film and television productions. Her most notable lead roles include \"Amanda Bloom\" in [[Abc family|ABC Family]]'s ''[[Kyle XY]]'', Alex Bell in MTV's ''[[My Super Psycho Sweet 16]]'' comedy-horror trilogy, and \"Char Chamberlin\" in ABC Family's ''[[The Lying Game]]''. Her most notable guest stars include roles in ''[[Stargate SG-1]], [[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]], [[Psych]], [[Devious Maids]],'' and ''[[Dear White People (TV series)|Dear White People]].''{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==Personal life==\nOn October 13, 2017, Prout announced her engagement to [[Development executive|television development executive]] Matt Zien.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BaNTmIuBWIf/|title=Kirsten Prout on Instagram|work=[[Instagram]]|date=October 13, 2017|accessdate=2017-10-25}}</ref> They were married on November 6, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BbMqYMlBNgs/|title=Kirsten Prout on Instagram|work=[[Instagram]]|date=November 7, 2017|accessdate=2017-11-07}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2001 \n| ''[[Mindstorm (film)|Mindstorm]]'' \n| Young Tracy Wellman \n|\n|-\n| 2001 \n| ''De grot''\n| Julie \n| Uncredited\n|-\n| 2005 \n| ''[[Elektra (2005 film)|Elektra]]'' \n| Abigail \"Abby\" Miller \n| \n|-\n| 2008 \n| ''Class Savage'' \n| Julye \n| Short film\n|-\n| 2010 \n| ''[[The Twilight Saga: Eclipse]]'' \n| Lucy \n|\n|-\n| 2013 \n| ''[[No Clue]]'' \n| Reese \n| \n|-\n| 2014 \n| ''[[Joy Ride 3: Roadkill]]'' \n| Jewel McCaul \n| Direct to video\n|-\n| 2015 \n| ''Even Lambs Have Teeth'' \n| Sloane\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Captured''\n| Nicole \n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2000 \n| ''[[The Linda McCartney Story]]'' \n| Stella \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[First Wave (TV series)|First Wave]]''\n| Emily\n| Episode: \"Wednesday's Child\"\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Once Upon a Christmas (film)|Once Upon a Christmas]]'' \n| Brittney Morgan \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Mysterious Ways (TV series)|Mysterious Ways]]''\n| Lindsay Kasper\n| Episode: \"Wonderful\" \n|-\n| 2001 \n| ''The Wedding Dress'' \n| Stella Carver \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Twice Upon a Christmas]]'' \n| Brittney Morgan \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Jeremiah (TV series)|Jeremiah]]'' \n| Elayna \n| Episode: \"The Touch\"\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Beyond Belief: Fact or Fiction]]''\n| Katie\n| Episode: \"Shared Vision\"\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[The Dead Zone (TV series)|The Dead Zone]]''\n| Susan Reed\n| Episode: \"Here There Be Monsters\"\n|-\n| 2003 \n| ''[[Stargate SG-1]]'' \n| Nesa \n| Episode: \"Birthright\"\n|-\n| 2004 \n| ''The Love Crimes of Gillian Guess'' \n| Amanda Guess \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Cold Squad]]''\n| Ashley\n| Episode: \"The Filth\"\n|-\n| 2006\u20132009 \n| ''[[Kyle XY]]'' \n| Amanda Bloom \n| Main role, 39 episodes\n|-\n| 2007 \n| ''Witness to Murder'' \n| Samantha Cooper \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Meteor Storm]]'' \n| Kara \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Locked Away'' \n| Taylin \n| Television film\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Seven Deadly Sins'' \n| Miranda Stevens\n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[My Super Psycho Sweet 16: Part 2]]'' \n| Alex Bell\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2011\u20132012 \n| ''[[The Lying Game]]'' \n| Charlotte \"Char\" Chamberlin \n| Main role, 12 episodes\n|-\n| 2012 \n| ''[[My Super Psycho Sweet 16: Part 3]]'' \n| Alex Bell \n