cular DNA viruses in stool samples of wild-living chimpanzees | journal = The Journal of General Virology | volume = 91 | issue = Pt 1 | pages = 74\u201386 | date = January 2010 | pmid = 19759238 | pmc = 2887567 | doi = 10.1099/vir.0.015446-0 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Colson2012>{{cite journal | vauthors = Colson P, de Lamballerie X, Fournous G, Raoult D | title = Reclassification of giant viruses composing a fourth domain of life in the new order Megavirales | journal = Intervirology | volume = 55 | issue = 5 | pages = 321\u2013332 | year = 2012 | pmid = 22508375 | doi = 10.1159/000336562 | doi-access = free }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Davison2002>{{cite journal | vauthors = Davison AJ | title = Evolution of the herpesviruses | journal = Veterinary Microbiology | volume = 86 | issue = 1\u20132 | pages = 69\u201388 | date = April 2002 | pmid = 11888691 | doi = 10.1016/S0378-1135(01)00492-8 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Dayaram2012>{{cite journal | vauthors = Dayaram A, Opong A, J\u00e4schke A, Hadfield J, Baschiera M, Dobson RC, Offei SK, Shepherd DN, Martin DP, Varsani A | title = Molecular characterisation of a novel cassava associated circular ssDNA virus | journal = Virus Research | volume = 166 | issue = 1\u20132 | pages = 130\u2013135 | date = June 2012 | pmid = 22465471 | doi = 10.1016/j.virusres.2012.03.009 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Dayaram2013>{{cite journal | vauthors = Dayaram A, Goldstien S, Zawar-Reza P, Gomez C, Harding JS, Varsani A | title = Novel ssDNA virus recovered from estuarine Mollusc (''Amphibola crenata'') whose replication associated protein (Rep) shares similarities with Rep-like sequences of bacterial origin | journal = The Journal of General Virology | volume = 94 | issue = Pt 5 | pages = 1104\u20131110 | date = May 2013 | pmid = 23364192 | doi = 10.1099/vir.0.050088-0 | doi-access = free }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Delwart2012>{{cite journal | vauthors = Delwart E, Li L | title = Rapidly expanding genetic diversity and host range of the Circoviridae viral family a