{"title_page": "Dan Croll", "text_new": "{{short description|British singer-songwriter|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Dan Croll\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Dan Croll - Way Back When Festival 2017 - Alexander Kellner - 3.jpg\n| caption          = Dan Croll in 2017\n| birth_name       = Daniel Francis Croll\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1990|07|18|24}}\n| birth_place      = [[Newcastle-under-Lyme]], England\n| origin           = [[Stoke-on-Trent]], Staffordshire, England\n| genre            = [[Indie rock]], [[folktronica]], [[pop rock]], [[indie pop]]\n| occupation       = Singer-songwriter\n| instruments      = Guitar, trumpet, piano, bass guitar, percussion\n| years_active     = 2010\u2014present\n| label            = Communion Records\n| associated_acts  = Eye Emma Jedi, Dire Wolf, Jethro Fox\n| website          = {{URL|dancroll.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Daniel Francis Croll''' (born 18 July 1990) is a British singer-songwriter born in [[Newcastle-under-Lyme]], Staffordshire, England. He moved to [[Liverpool]] when he was 18 to attend the [[Liverpool Institute for Performing Arts]] (LIPA). While at LIPA, he won the national Songwriter of the Year award from the [[Musicians' Benevolent Fund]]<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-12424372/ | title=LIPA student wins writing award|newspaper=BBC News | date=14 February 2011 | accessdate=14 January 2013}}</ref> and was one of eight students picked to have a one-to-one with LIPA founder [[Paul McCartney|Sir Paul McCartney]]. He is currently signed to Communion Music.\n\n==Early releases==\nCroll's first release was as part of the [[Communion Music|Communion]] record label's compilation ''New Faces'', released on 23 April 2012. Communion have supported Croll both with this release and promoting many of his early live performances.\n\n==2012 \u2013 present==\n\nCroll signed to Turn First Records at the start of 2012. His debut single, \"From Nowhere,\" was released worldwide on 24 September 2012 via Turn First / Racquet Records (Croll's own imprint) as a digital download and limited 7\". \"From Nowhere\" spent 3 days at the top of the [[Hype Machine]] popular charts, was playlisted in the UK on [[BBC 6 Music]], [[XFM]] and [[Amazing Radio]], and received spot plays on [[BBC Radio 1]].  The song also received airplay in the US, reaching #36 on the Billboard Alternative chart. Croll was named a ''Guardian'' New Band of the Day<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/nov/08/new-band-dan-croll | title=New band of the day \u2013 Dan Croll (No 1,390)|newspaper=[[The Guardian]] | date=8 November 2011| accessdate=14 January 2013| last1=Lester| first1=Paul}}</ref> in November 2012 and described as \"Paul Simon jamming with Prince. Very nice\".\n\nCroll released his second single \"Compliment Your Soul\" in March 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dan Croll \u2013 Compliment Your Soul|url=http://www.indieshuffle.com/dan-croll-compliment-your-soul/|publisher=Indie Shuffle|accessdate=3 March 2013}}</ref> This was followed up by the release of \"In/Out\" in July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|first=Dan |last=Croll|url=http://www.indieshuffle.com/dan-croll/|publisher=Indie Shuffle|accessdate=12 July 2013|title=Dan Croll \u2013 In/Out}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 October 2013, Croll released the song \"Home\" on his own [[VEVO]] channel on YouTube.\n\nOn 29 October 2013, during an on-air [[Virgin Radio]] interview, Croll confirmed he had finished recording his full-length debut album. The LP was expected to be released early in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://virginmobilefeed.com/on-air-with-abbey-1029-feat-dan-croll/|title=A Simpler Way to Buy Mobile - Virgin Mobile|website=virginmobilefeed.com}}</ref>\n\nHis song \"Compliment Your Soul\" was included in the soundtrack for the video game ''[[FIFA 14]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=EA Sports revealed the soundtrack for the video game FIFA 14 |url=http://www.utfifas.com/news/EA-Sports-revealed-the-soundtrack-for-the-video-game-FIFA-14.html |website=www.utfifas.com/ |accessdate=24 October 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331010834/http://www.utfifas.com/news/EA-Sports-revealed-the-soundtrack-for-the-video-game-FIFA-14.html |archivedate=31 March 2014}}</ref> As well as FIFA, a remix of \"From Nowhere,\" titled \"From Nowhere (Baardsen Remix)\", was featured on the soundtrack of ''[[Grand Theft Auto V]]''. The song was featured on one of the game's radio stations, [[Radio Mirror Park]], and in the official trailer of the game regarding its release on PC, and the next-generation Xbox One and PlayStation 4 consoles.\n\nIn November 2013 he announced, during a concert in [[Camden Town]], London, that his first album ''[[Sweet Disarray]]'', would be released on 10 March 2014.\n\nOn 19 April 2014 for [[Record Store Day]], Croll released a limited 10\" orange vinyl featuring 2 unreleased songs. Side A featured \"Hello My Baby\" (featuring [[Ladysmith Black Mambazo]]) which was backed with \"Ever at Your Side\". Croll went to [[Durban]] to record \"Hello My Baby\" with the group. The limited vinyl was released in independent record stores on the day.\n\nIn September 2015, Croll released the single \"One of Us.\" In June 2016, Croll announced that he had signed with Communion Music. The [[Electro (music)|electro]]-song \"Swim\" was released on 25 August 2016 through the label.<ref>{{cite web|title=Swim - Single by Dan Croll on Apple Music|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/swim-single/id1147456968|website=iTunes|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hunt|first1=El|title=Dan Croll returns with 'Swim'|url=http://diymag.com/2016/08/31/dan-croll-returns-with-swim|website=DIY|accessdate=1 September 2016|date=31 August 2016}}</ref> The music video for \"Swim\" was released on 31 August 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dan Croll - Swim (Official Video)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M34VETZL7uA|accessdate=1 September 2016|date=31 August 2016}}</ref> Croll's second studio album ''Emerging Adulthood'' was released on 21 July 2017.<ref name=\"ea\"/>\n\nIn early 2020, multiple new songs were released, and a third album named ''Grand Plan'' was announced on 15 April via social media<ref>{{cite web|title=Dan Croll Announces New Album GRAND PLAN|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Dan-Croll-Announces-New-Album-GRAND-PLAN-20200415|accessdate=25 April 2020|date=15 April 2020}}</ref>. It is scheduled to be released 21 August 2020.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Peak positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Irish Albums Chart|IRE]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Scottish Albums Chart|SCO]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Sweet Disarray]]''\n|\n* Released: 10 March 2014\n* Label: [[Deram Records|Deram]], [[Universal Music Group|Universal]]\n* Formats: [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| 26 || \u2014 || 53\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Emerging Adulthood''<ref name=\"ea\">{{cite web|title=Emerging Adulthood|work=[[iTunes]].Apple (GB)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/emerging-adulthood/id1214384018|accessdate=2017-03-26}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: 21 July 2017\n* Label: Communion Group \n* Formats: CD, digital download\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Work\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"From Nowhere\"\n|\n* Released: 24 September 2012<ref name=\"ep\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/from-nowhere-remixes-ep/id562480455 |title='From Nowhere' by Dan Croll |publisher=[[iTunes]] |accessdate=14 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121213091150/https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/from-nowhere-remixes-ep/id562480455 |archivedate=13 December 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n* Label: Turn First Records (UK), Racquet Records (UK), [[Capitol Records]] (US)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/triple-a/future-releases |title=Future Releases on Triple A (AAA) Radio Stations |publisher=All Access Music Group |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Nt2WGM2u?url=http://www.allaccess.com/triple-a/future-releases |archivedate=7 March 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n* Format: Digital download, [[Gramophone record|vinyl]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Compliment Your Soul\"\n|\n* Released: 1 April 2013\n* Label: Turn First Records (UK), Racquet Records (UK)\n* Format: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"In/Out\"\n|\n* Released: 12 July 2013\n* Label: Turn First Records (UK), [[Deram Records]], [[Universal Music Group]]\n* Format: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Home\"\n|\n* Released: 1 December 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/home-single/id736211832|title=Home - Single by Dan Croll on Apple Music|website=iTunes}}</ref>\n* Label: Deram Records, Universal Music Group\n* Format: Digital download, vinyl\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Hello My Baby <small>(featuring [[Ladysmith Black Mambazo]])</small>/Ever at Your Side\"\n|\n* Released: 19 April 2014\n* Label: Deram Records, Capitol Records\n* Format: Vinyl\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Nobody Knows\"<br /><small>(featuring The Very Best)</small>\n|\n* Released: 30 May 2014\n* Label: Deram Records, Capitol Records\n* Format: Vinyl\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"One of Us\"\n|\n* Released: 14 October 2015\n* Label: Deram Records, Capitol Records\n* Format: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Swim\"\n|\n* Released: 25 August 2016\n* Label: Communion Music\n* Format: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Be Alone\"\n|\n*Released: 13 December 2016\n*Label: ??\n*Format: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Away From Today\"\n| \n* Release: 23 January 2017\n* Label: Communion Music\n* Format: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Bad Boy\"\n| \n* Release: 1 June 2017\n* Label: Communion Music\n* Format: Digital download\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Croll, Dan}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:British singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:People from Newcastle-under-Lyme]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Liverpool Institute for Performing Arts]]\n[[Category:21st-century British singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British singer-songwriter|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Dan Croll\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Dan Croll - Way Back When Festival 2017 - Alexander Kellner - 3.jpg\n| caption          = Dan Croll in 2017\n| birth_name       = Daniel Francis Croll\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1990|07|18|24}}\n| birth_place      = [[Newcastle-under-Lyme]], England\n| origin           = [[Stoke-on-Trent]], Staffordshire, England\n| genre            = [[Indie rock]], [[folktronica]], [[pop rock]], [[indie pop]]\n| occupation       = Singer-songwriter\n| instruments      = Guitar, trumpet, piano, bass guitar, percussion\n| years_active     = 2010\u2014present\n| label            = Communion Records\n| associated_acts  = Eye Emma Jedi, Dire Wolf, Jethro Fox\n| website          = {{URL|dancroll.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Daniel Francis Croll''' (born 18 July 1990) is a British singer-songwriter born in [[Newcastle-under-Lyme]], Staffordshire, England. He moved to [[Liverpool]] when he was 18 to attend the [[Liverpool Institute for Performing Arts]] (LIPA). While at LIPA, he won the national Songwriter of the Year award from the [[Musicians' Benevolent Fund]]<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-12424372/ | title=LIPA student wins writing award|newspaper=BBC News | date=14 February 2011 | accessdate=14 January 2013}}</ref> and was one of eight students picked to have a one-to-one with LIPA founder [[Paul McCartney|Sir Paul McCartney]]. He is currently signed to Communion Music.\n\n==Early releases==\nCroll's first release was as part of the [[Communion Music|Communion]] record label's compilation ''New Faces'', released on 23 April 2012. Communion have supported Croll both with this release and promoting many of his early live performances.\n\n==2012 \u2013 present==\n\nCroll signed to Turn First Records at the start of 2012. His debut single, \"From Nowhere,\" was released worldwide on 24 September 2012 via Turn First / Racquet Records (Croll's own imprint) as a digital download and limited 7\". \"From Nowhere\" spent 3 days at the top of the [[Hype Machine]] popular charts, was playlisted in the UK on [[BBC 6 Music]], [[XFM]] and [[Amazing Radio]], and received spot plays on [[BBC Radio 1]].  The song also received airplay in the US, reaching #36 on the Billboard Alternative chart. Croll was named a ''Guardian'' New Band of the Day<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/nov/08/new-band-dan-croll | title=New band of the day \u2013 Dan Croll (No 1,390)|newspaper=[[The Guardian]] | date=8 November 2011| accessdate=14 January 2013| last1=Lester| first1=Paul}}</ref> in November 2012 and described as \"Paul Simon jamming with Prince. Very nice\".\n\nCroll released his second single \"Compliment Your Soul\" in March 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dan Croll \u2013 Compliment Your Soul|url=http://www.indieshuffle.com/dan-croll-compliment-your-soul/|publisher=Indie Shuffle|accessdate=3 March 2013}}</ref> This was followed up by the release of \"In/Out\" in July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|first=Dan |last=Croll|url=http://www.indieshuffle.com/dan-croll/|publisher=Indie Shuffle|accessdate=12 July 2013|title=Dan Croll \u2013 In/Out}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 October 2013, Croll released the song \"Home\" on his own [[VEVO]] channel on YouTube.\n\nOn 29 October 2013, during an on-air [[Virgin Radio]] interview, Croll confirmed he had finished recording his full-length debut album. The LP was expected to be released early in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://virginmobilefeed.com/on-air-with-abbey-1029-feat-dan-croll/|title=A Simpler Way to Buy Mobile - Virgin Mobile|website=virginmobilefeed.com}}</ref>\n\nHis song \"Compliment Your Soul\" was included in the soundtrack for the video game ''[[FIFA 14]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=EA Sports revealed the soundtrack for the video game FIFA 14 |url=http://www.utfifas.com/news/EA-Sports-revealed-the-soundtrack-for-the-video-game-FIFA-14.html |website=www.utfifas.com/ |accessdate=24 October 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331010834/http://www.utfifas.com/news/EA-Sports-revealed-the-soundtrack-for-the-video-game-FIFA-14.html |archivedate=31 March 2014}}</ref> As well as FIFA, a remix of \"From Nowhere,\" titled \"From Nowhere (Baardsen Remix)\", was featured on the soundtrack of ''[[Grand Theft Auto V]]''. The song was featured on one of the game's radio stations, [[Radio Mirror Park]], and in the official trailer of the game regarding its release on PC, and the next-generation Xbox One and PlayStation 4 consoles.\n\nIn November 2013 he announced, during a concert in [[Camden Town]], London, that his first album ''[[Sweet Disarray]]'', would be released on 10 March 2014.\n\nOn 19 April 2014 for [[Record Store Day]], Croll released a limited 10\" orange vinyl featuring 2 unreleased songs. Side A featured \"Hello My Baby\" (featuring [[Ladysmith Black Mambazo]]) which was backed with \"Ever at Your Side\". Croll went to [[Durban]] to record \"Hello My Baby\" with the group. The limited vinyl was released in independent record stores on the day.\n\nIn September 2015, Croll released the single \"One of Us.\" In June 2016, Croll announced that he had signed with Communion Music. The [[Electro (music)|electro]]-song \"Swim\" was released on 25 August 2016 through the label.<ref>{{cite web|title=Swim - Single by Dan Croll on Apple Music|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/swim-single/id1147456968|website=iTunes|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hunt|first1=El|title=Dan Croll returns with 'Swim'|url=http://diymag.com/2016/08/31/dan-croll-returns-with-swim|website=DIY|accessdate=1 September 2016|date=31 August 2016}}</ref> The music video for \"Swim\" was released on 31 August 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dan Croll - Swim (Official Video)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M34VETZL7uA|accessdate=1 September 2016|date=31 August 2016}}</ref> Croll's second studio album ''Emerging Adulthood'' was released on 21 July 2017.<ref name=\"ea\"/>\n\nIn early 2020, multiple new songs were released, and a third album named ''Grand Plan'' was announced on April 15 via social media<ref>{{cite web|title=Dan Croll Announces New Album GRAND PLAN|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Dan-Croll-Announces-New-Album-GRAND-PLAN-20200415|accessdate=25 April 2020|date=15 April 2020}}</ref>. It is scheduled to be released 21 August 2020.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Peak positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Irish Albums Chart|IRE]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Scottish Albums Chart|SCO]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Sweet Disarray]]''\n|\